title: Approaches to Learning and Play
subject: Preschool Early Learning and Development Standards (2024-)

document.title: Preschool - Maine's Early Learning and Development Standards

48D06527C79A4D5797367B84C4D1FF8C.description:
With prompting and support,
children assume the roles of
characters, using props and
language to tell or retell a
story.

C16CF0EDA5B84F71B218F07A844FC184.description:
Creates characters through
physical movement, gesture,
sound, speech and facial
expressions.

B5DB3E631A704C55A7660E9551B53BBE.description:
Uses pretend play to
represent known or
anticipated situations.

0F238E7E27B34A2AB5A887880F25321F.description:
Represents fantasy and
real-life experiences through pretend play and may use
props.

719832D554C2455290584DD7D0510C24.description:
Uses inanimate objects
for other than their
intended purpose to create
representations of real-life
objects or activities.

C13B4E028FFC462DB7CE756829C7F530.description:
Mimics movements, sounds, and expressions of real-life
experiences.

679EADB8FBED439E817205B013FB7AC1.description:
Begins to role play real life
experiences (e.g., pretend to
listen to your heart).

33F95B38552D4542A9CB3ABD7462E55E.description:
Begins to use inanimate
objects to represent real life
objects (e.g. uses banana as a
phone).

FA176FFCAE5D4B9A9458D86D2B1BAA5C.description:
Explores music and
instruments from other
cultures.

F1732F9CF9D14A78AA155E7CDCD6D80C.description:
Uses musical instruments to
imitate and improvise songs,
melodies, and patterns.

8002BABCD07B44AEA30749D3DAA99EF0.description:
Sings songs with varied lyrics
and patterns.

406D633E43324130AD35CF79DF752E8A.description:
Increasing ability to adapt to
pitch and sounds.

3678D30A7BA64B98881DBCEE8B4BD945.description:
Shows increasing ability to
recognize tempo changes
and different styles of music.

2ABD74E594CA41B99CA97E5A11B8BE94.description:
Uses body percussion to
demonstrate beat and tempo.

3D4DE569C78547BFAE599C366E13F549.description:
Experiments with a variety of
musical instruments.

988427F8D9824952B413150391DB7B5E.description:
Imitates sounds that
demonstrate musical
awareness.

19B55FC5C9704FC2B2B0E0B0501C4ADA.description:
Participates with simple
songs that have a rhythm and
pattern.

C992A5F3B2E0420D9EC5D58F26EC7A89.description:
Participates in slow and fast
tempo as well as low and
high sounds.

126ADF54065F407DAE90EA96FDF2ACA5.description:
Claps hands to keep the beat
to a song.

F87AF9B66AAD4222ABA996EDEADE9EF3.description:
Engages in and collaborates
during group creative
movement/dance.

01AC30E5F578410E98D7F32051B2598A.description:
Combines creative movement
with sound, song/chants and/
or instruments to express
ideas or retell a story.

DF33FD12D9604BC5B17CCCD5EA638A4B.description:
Uses creative movement that
expresses an idea or feeling.

78671C5E9A214E38ABC7733CE7ED9407.description:
Moves in response to
different styles of music.

85538CBA2908439FA3C8DE2D87CAC518.description:
Begins to participate in group
movement/dance.

784EC911C99042F89E6D73C2B5F23230.description:
Begins to connect body
movements to music, song or
creative ideas.

165F716D52F047648331E5FF50CAB3CA.description:
Develops increasing body
control, body awareness
during creative movement.

DE893FDED5034BEC8D763688468298A6.description:
Participates in a variety
of rhythmic and creative
movement experiences.

0740AA9D0D75494FBAB08AB903C8C391.description:
Observes, discusses and may
utilize multicultural art styles
and materials.

DCED7CAC84734E70B61272ED74571276.description:
Explores diverse art forms,
elements and styles for
representing ideas, creative
thought and to support
learning in other learning
domains.

35FA016BCC6E4FE48AA0E2603F29F03D.description:
Listens, comments and shows
appreciation for the art
expression of others.

D9978A69AB5F4F49801E50CE2C87F1D7.description:
Describes the process and
style of personal artwork.

EBABDEF52DA24BACBD72FEF6B9F18415.description:
Explores and utilizes art
materials appropriately.

40D4DE9001AD4988B27E4C0A3558CC34.description:
Progresses in abilities to
create with a variety of media
that reflect more detail,
uniqueness, and/or realism.

1DF3A922433345CD81A4DB7C30085357.description:
Works cooperatively to
create drawings, paintings,
sculptures, and other art
projects.

2F7DBE2AF23B48C1B7138BF34B2FC34A.description:
Shows increasing
engagement in art materials
to express ideas and interests.

FCE1FB332AE345AFB17AC17530F51B62.description:
Shows interest or participates
in different art media and
materials in a variety of ways
for creative expression and
representation.

89EB0738207D4C938D54A4AA28B73BC5.description:
Explores multicultural art
styles and materials.

320C227A34714D7EBBDCF6A9086A8219.description:
With support begins to
make comments or share
observations of the art
expression of others.

879A2E8C121B4DBDA504310CCB1D4EAA.description:
Begins to identify artwork to
be shared with others.

40595EFDF879406C83297733E33D3441.description:
With support talks about
creative process.

27C8E18DC9EF4B0DBEFFD078839C4D57.description:
Explores a variety of art
elements and materials to
represent creative thought,
life experiences and real
things in the environment.

D6139EF37067493EAA4C7F7394D1462F.description:
Uses and explores art
materials to stimulate
the senses. Uses sensory
information to create works
of art.

0FBA671B18B4419B91C015B22D940F8C.description:
Uses color, lines and shapes
to represent and express
ideas.

EC0A449990AE4617AE6E5CAA5D57A583.description:
Shares art materials and
space. Begins to work
collaboratively with peers on
artworks.

C0B61FC720724E08A2BA1D232C0B62E0.description:
Uses self-selected materials
to engage in art experiences.

B289CD744D114B30BF81A1177E416E23.description:
Creativity, Invention, and Imagination: involves finding new ways to express ideas, use objects, and solve problems through visual arts, movement, dance, music and
dramatic play.

65EF73EAEDAC46BEB8BDD941783CF4B5.description:
Is able to manage a change in
rules or accepts the ideas of
peers during play.

83AF91BB84DD4D4DA6CE317DAF187C5D.description:
Considers, predicts and
implements different
approaches to carrying out a
task.

4FF2D9B4E73E42B1A50FAA7E01A1E687.description:
Independently alters
approach to tasks or problem
when initial approach does not work.

BB958CDAA04F409C9F35E552F9DC5591.description:
Can adjust emotions and
behavior to changes.

FABA2E3CDFD74E58A5B051CE18F210C4.description:
Seeks guidance from adults
and/or accepts suggestions to
try different approaches and
solutions to tasks, problems
and interactions with peers.

D64EB920BA7B43B2964BD443C3A3ADE7.description:
Accepts more than one
solution to a question, task,
or problem.

BD4C34AB214E4C9AA1F8CC87CCB77A2A.description:
Generates and shares ideas
during social interactions and
dramatic play.

8ABCA1DB5A124C15A6BCB639CED9EA23.description:
Maintains communication
and problem solving skills
when finding a solution to
conflicts.

DBA76D56BBCF40C4BCA3CD840E48039A.description:
Recognizes that problems
exist and learns how to
resolve simple conflicts
independently or
collaboratively.

C6378502DC4645BC843948430A44DE54.description:
Predicts when something
might be a problem or
challenge.

499C26AF9AE74CBCBE95ABC7387498AA.description:
Begins to use appropriate
communication or action
when conflicts arise.

DAD46AC18E3143B89EAEE670445B426E.description:
With prompting and support
begins to attempt to solve a
problem.

BF139A64145B4CA7A782131372DACE07.description:
Recognizes when something
might be a problem or
challenge.

37BF444005F646C3927BFED84B4EFD86.description:
Discusses or documents
important aspects of an
experience and identifies
what was learned.

3408400EB7CC4EBF858D06D33D99FDE3.description:
Draws on information to be
able to review and anticipate
to make if-then connections
and contemplate what if
situations that have not
actually occurred.

13C98981EFD441F6821509F1B2231B95.description:
Discovers and finds patterns
and relationships.

3E581E6879E540808563C7F72A32EE2B.description:
Applies prior experiences,
senses, and knowledge to
new learning situations.

8510AEBA73B8477887F3E41DFC9AD40D.description:
Thinks about multiple
options, choices and decides
if they are useful and if not,
tries another.

0CF4CF681B944D79AC8FDE00EC5F2598.description:
Explains part or all of the
problem and the exploration
to adults or peers.

BF4430A330C44FE888D76AD084A1C773.description:
Makes predictions about
what will happen next.

531432477D2A4824ACECF7884E9A870A.description:
Increasingly applies learning
from prior experiences and understanding to new
learning situations.

8996DF52BF3042F59228E90ADD0576B1.description:
Notices changes and
accomplishments from
experimentation and trial and
error.

FEE4125C4EA54178A40F9121AB8DB56D.description:
Chooses to take
opportunities to explore
a variety of materials and
experiences, seeking out new
challenges.

A334677A8AD74B3AB8E7085C7DCAA909.description:
Approaches tasks and
activities with increasing
flexibility, complexity,
imagination and inventiveness.

5C7E40B1EA0148BB990556D98F1826EF.description:
Carries out investigations
using familiar and new
strategies, tools, or sources of
information.

0DA9BF08704C43149D4EF14065E41C0D.description:
Discovers and investigates
ideas, tasks, experiences that
interest and amaze them.

ACC5EDDF83C248B6BEA7E21FCC9D1A7E.description:
Explores a variety of materials
and experiences.

673ED1990F6C47078AAE80BD2344E2A2.description:
Describes what was learned
from an activity.

BEF48A8244A447B68678277BF3D8EFB6.description:
Tries new ways to accomplish
tasks.

68ED8945D5B0414C8D00E76B687F763E.description:
Uses senses to gather information and
understanding about
materials and ideas.

8CBAAF52A2FB4584B739CB989B7E2307.description:
Begins to discover and
investigate ideas, task,
experiences that interest and
amaze them.

25ED8AD9D7914468A87DC46438A5584F.description:
Sets goals, develops plans,
and follows through with
self directed projects with
increasing independence
and/or collaboration.

90F6B1D80F894304ACB9781BFDCA1FB7.description:
Invents projects and works on
them with little assistance.

727915CC724C4FCB89C813251BC15E23.description:
Can identify and seek
materials, strategies and
tools they need to complete
activities and tasks.

410A800F37624E4AACDC2EFE3BBC763A.description:
Independently seeks, accepts
or offers help or information
for further understanding.

9425734ECFA4468CB9B94E0B19C89346.description:
Offers to help adults or peers
with daily tasks.

2827F7C2F38C44DFB8F429443356B7D2.description:
Tells the difference
between appropriate and
inappropriate risk-taking.

CC242373AAE34457840411938E8E4781.description:
Asks to join in play already in
progress.

8E5FAADFBBDF4FDB8BA80CA2886A9C75.description:
Demonstrates ability to make
independent choices.

9781993C48864AACB58DD9FC2AF9B60B.description:
Expresses interest in a
widening range of topics and
ideas.

111BCECF78F848FAB56115D5718EBC48.description:
Shows interest in how and
why others do things.

6D4F22BC2BAD4FFA83C87D0A85C404F1.description:
Keeps trying and flexibly
adapts strategies when
encountering difficulties.

F47F0391071A46B2BCED46A0BC4914C9.description:
Chooses to repeat
experiences to build
competence and explore,
change and extend ideas.

F620E9858A3147349109AF05F8D5A9AC.description:
Chooses to leave a project
and return to it later
for follow through or
elaboration.

A3B4A28647E04821A11E2ACA01F66451.description:
Demonstrates resilience and
coping skills when faced
with reasonable challenges,
using an increased ability to
regulate frustration over time.

7E25738DEFE14238A521B403D8D3FFA6.description:
Works through challenges
with increasing independence
while engaged in self-selected
activities.

352BF9D11BC4497B90BBE9BBCE64456A.description:
Purposefully chooses,
engages and persists in play,
experiences and projects.

C8B26E9D835A4CD496F7786847306253.description:
Begins to set goals, develop
plans, and complete tasks.

7A48C92FA3484C7ABEC26DB6EC2DBE7B.description:
Sees simple tasks through to
completion.

75B4C57FE4F54EEAB484C184B32615D6.description:
Can increasingly work
through challenges and
frustrations in play with adult
support.

608BDBDB769B4F7FB076A01179690F71.description:
During times of distraction,
maintains concentration with
increased focus.

6CEF5CDCCB274019BC8EE4701113456F.description:
Engages in a variety of
activities through a play
period.

3DC08980FE53408A87D30423112D9BBA.description:
Consistently remains
engaged in self-directed play
even with distractions, can
maintain focus and return to
an activity after a break.

7E3D1266E19847E58DBEEB0D89838291.description:
Participates with pleasure,
enthusiasm and dedication in
self chosen activities.

42174A8549CE4C70874C3C994A9C01E8.description:
Has capacity to maintain
involvement and
concentration for a
meaningful period of time.

D5F409904AFA4C4E82B6049BB1177DE2.description:
Eagerly chooses to be
involved in a variety of tasks
and activities.

6B514978920E4C16ACEE9B17C27E4172.description:
Mindset: involves children’s developing ability to regulate their emotions, thoughts and behavior to enable them to act in positive ways toward a
goal.
